- Use PHP 8.3+ features where appropriate
- The code should be strictly typed by using PHP type hints and with `declare(strict_types=1);`
- Always use explicit return type declarations
- Use appropriate PHP type hints for method parameters
- Document complex types in PHPDoc blocks
- Provide complete documentation for classes, methods, and properties
- Document parameters with correct types and descriptions
- Include `@return`, `@throws`, and `@deprecated` tags as needed
- Everything should be thoroughly logged with the debug log level with all the detail to debug the potential problem included in the log line
- Favor functional paradigms over object-oriented ones, favor composition over inheritance
- Follow PCR-12 coding standards